46:14.620 --> 46:17.860
Yudkowsky calls this the trap of under-constrained abstractions.

46:18.000 --> 46:19.480
Under-constrained abstractions.

46:19.560 --> 46:20.780
Let's use a famous example.

46:21.060 --> 46:21.720
Moore's Law.

46:21.920 --> 46:23.520
Okay, everyone knows Moore's Law.

46:23.520 --> 46:31.240
Right. Moore's Law is the historical observation that the number of transistors you can fit on a computer chip doubles roughly every two years.

