We started an hour ago with a simple, deceptively basic mathematical grammar.

01:00:58.120 --> 01:01:06.380
A bounded region with a rule, an incoming perturbation, a violent internal collapse, and a new stable state that remembers its past.

01:01:06.600 --> 01:01:07.820
The admissibility principle.

01:01:07.820 --> 01:01:22.340
And we've seen how that exact same sequence links the abstract lambda calculus of the 1930s to Hofstadter's blurry bundles of human memory, to the epigenetic destiny of a microscopic stem cell deciding to become a heartburn.

