A city doesn't die when its physical matter slowly degrades or its buildings get old.

01:02:46.900 --> 01:02:50.840
A city dies when its transport pathways lose coherent accessibility.

01:02:51.340 --> 01:02:52.240
When the system breaks down.

01:02:52.500 --> 01:02:54.640
When the garbage stops being collected.

01:02:55.280 --> 01:02:58.080
When the laws stop mapping to reality.

01:02:58.720 --> 01:03:01.460
When the system suffers from bundle degeneration.

01:03:01.680 --> 01:03:02.140
Bundle degenerates.

